x4freetext: Symmetric and asymmetric fission of 226-Ra induced by
RaF2 sample of about 100 microg weight, made by
- for measurement with 5-15 MeV neutrons, as mentioned
targets of Ra-226 and U-238 of 9 mm diameter were
placed at 20mm distance from neutron source. Ra sample
Ra sample of 312 +-7 microg weight, 8 mm diameter,
placed at 10 mm distance from neutron source at 0 deg
angle relative to deuteron beam; U-238 sample of the
same diameter was used to define integral neutron beam;
RaCl2 samples on Ni foils of 400 microg/cm**2
thickness stacked , total weight 327 microg, diameter
7 mm; used for FF angular distribution measurement.
Mica track detector. For fission events counting.
Si detector of p-n type. For FF energy
Cf-252 spontaneous fission spectrum of FF was measured
for calibration in experiment with neutrons of 5-15 MeV
U-238 fiss. c-s was used for normalization in
U-238 counting was used to define integral neutron
beam at measurement in 3.6-7.1 MeV energy range.
